      <section id="id1165292322259">
        <title>Phonics</title>
        <list id="id1165292817486" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>For you to learn: </item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1165292823709">When “e” comes after a word with a as in apple, the sound changes.</para>
        <list id="id1165292823714" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>Read.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1165292750880">ate, plate, take, bake, game, name, gave, save, wave</para>
        <list id="id1165292674119" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>When “e” comes after a word with o as in orange, the sound changes.</item>
          <item>Read.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1165292474092">rose, nose, home, stone, smoke, hope, rope</para>
        <list id="id1165292415010" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>When “e” comes after a word with i as in ink, the sound changes.</item>
          <item>Read.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1165292302146">nine, smile, five, hive, kite, wife, life</para>
        <list id="id1165292822517" list-type="bulleted">
          <item>When “e” comes after a word with u as in umbrella, the sound changes.</item>
          <item>Read.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id1165292473045">use, fuse, tube, tune</para>
